Text.Value: What are you really asking, friend of Gortash?

EditorData.NodeContext: with an unexpected edge of intimidation

Text.Value: What do you have for sale?
Heavens no! I'm just the humble proprietor. Avery Sonshal, at your service. Descendant of the great Felogyr Sonshal.
Or perhaps the delicate simplicity of a perfectly crafted torch is more to your taste?
I have a special sample, available just for you, if you wish.
Which begs the question - what business do you have masquerading as a servant of Lord Gortash?
Are you Felogyr?
Exceptional quality, if I do say so myself. The Gondians will know it when they see it.
Anything that can be lit, flamed, or fired up! Smokepowder is a beautiful mistress, she will not be limited to one form, and she is quite malleable in the right hands.
And if it's not a firework - do whatever you like.
And for gods' sakes have a little discretion.
Question me again and your body will never be found.
I'd like to see what you have for sale.
*ROAR!*
Now get out of my sight.
I'll take that free sample now, please.
Has he, now? Then the latest update I sent did not arrive?
I don't know what kind of covert operative you are, but you are a threat to all that is good in this city.
I see... Then he must not have received my update.
Leave.
That is no answer at all.
If you are some sort of covert operative, you're a bad one.
See for yourself!
Excellent! Now remember - Felogyr's Fireworks accepts no liability for singed nails, toasted eyelashes, loss of limbs, scalded torsos, or blown-off heads.

EditorData.NodeContext: Uplifting, as if these weren't horrible side effects of having your face blown off by fireworks. Paced like a Terms and Conditions section of a radio ad.

Text.Value: I assure you that is quite impossible. I delivered it myself.
Let's see what you have in stock.
And what does Uncle Felogyr always say?
Browse responsibly now!
A-ha! You must be Arfur's friend.
I'm not sure yet. Can I see what you have for sale?
Gortash sent me to check on your latest order.
Yes yes, he's just upstairs. But only one flight - if you get to the top, you've gone too far.

EditorData.NodeContext: verbal equivalent of teasingly wagging a finger (and secretly meaning it when you're warning someone)

Text.Value: What do you want now?
You again. What do you want?
He's done nothing of the kind. I have his latest order in my pocket. And he already has his update on its progress.
Can I see what you have for sale?
Sure. Why not?
What else do you do for Lord Gortash?
I just want to trade.
I was just being nosy. Sorry.
Please enjoy responsibly! And nowhere near this establishment. Is there anything else I can do for you?
Remember - once it's lit, you commit!
Careful - my magic can be quite unpredictable, and I'd hate to see this place go up in flames.
Recall the password. 'Uncle Felogyr sent me'.
Once it's lit, you commit!

EditorData.NodeContext: chanted, pleased like a teacher's pet answering a question

Text.Value: This one will be very useful against any and all enemies of Gortash. Be sure to be clear of its explosion area.
How DARE you? I am exactly who I proclaim to be!
Tell me, what form will you have her in today?
Of course! Browse responsibly, now.
Very good. Browse responsibly, now.
He's upstairs. Only one floor up, mind.
Well, don't.
Forgive me - I did not know I had kept Gortash's humble servant waiting.
Your latest order is late. Gortash demands to know why.
I'm here to see Uncle Felogyr.
Oh, we trade in all sorts.
Leave.
Masquerading? Don't you recognise a servant of Gortash when you see one?
Faces. Hands. And eyebrows. How do we protect them?
Please - take this. On the house.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext:
Off-screen: hands us an item. 
Mindmeld FX/no lipsync

Text.Value: You may bring this message to him - everything is right on schedule. The next batch will be dispatched within a tenday.
I understand. We can't be too careful.
No. I'll just be on my way.
If you must.
(Keep your voice down.)

EditorData.NodeContext: a harsh whisper, NOT A MINMELD, spoken out loud

Text.Value: Just testing you. I'm interested in browsing your wares.
Have you tried the Lantanese candles?
I know this because I delivered it to him myself.
Browse responsibly!
(Browse as irresponsibly as you like. Just don't tell the other customers.)

EditorData.NodeContext: whispered, just to the player, conspirationally

Text.Value: What else? I don't know what you mean. We're purveyors of smokepowder.
Oh! Well why didn't you say so?
But you can call me Felogyr if you like. Helps spread the brand, see.

EditorData.NodeContext: conspirational and whimsical, like a verbal tap on the nose har har this is a lovely secret between us isn't it?

Text.Value: Is it really fireworks you sell to Gortash, or...?
Of course!
Whatever form best pleases Uncle Felogyr.
Recall the merchant's password. 'Uncle Felogyr sent me.'
Fabulously charismatic man though. Tips well.
Er... please, enjoy the store. If there's anything I can help with, do not hesitate to ask.

EditorData.NodeContext: a little quivery, afraid he misstepped

Text.Value: I believe that concludes this purchase order. We very much appreciate Lord Gortash's continued honouring of our humble establishment with his custom.
Very good!
Leave.
Oh heavens, no, not with him. I work for him. As I do for all of my most loyal customers.
Now - you there. What can I do for you?
We value his custom immensely, and the services of all those in his employ!
I'm here to visit Uncle Felogyr. He sent me, if you catch my drift.
*You feel an all-too-familiar squirm in the recesses of your mind. He has a tadpole.*
Watch for wind direction. Put on your gloves. Aaaaaand... alight at arm's length!
Nothing. Nothing at all.
Not in the mood for fireworks right now. Perhaps another time.
You mentioned Gortash when we first met - do you work with him?
Remember - face, hands, eyebrows. And once it's lit, you commit!

EditorData.NodeContext: abruptly cheerful in sales patter mode

Text.Value: Perhaps next time!
A-ha! A fellow friend of Gortash! Praise the Absolute.
Not a bother! Enjoy the shop.
Sorry. Sorry sorry sorry! Please. Don't tell your master I doubted you.

Synopsis: Dialog for Avery Sonshal, tadpoled proprietor of Felogyr's Fireworks. Sells harmless fireworks, alchemical supplies, and maybe some grenades. Helpful to the players if he recognizes them as also tadpoled.
